    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="132"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/436.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador to Japan</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You may at your discretion make public a statement to the effect that the
                    Governments having important commercial relations with China were early
                        notified<note n="1" xml:id="d132fn1">See telegram of Oct. 31, 1910, above,
                            <ref target="#pg_91">p. 91</ref>.</note> of the general features of the
                    currency <pb facs="0214" n="98" xml:id="pg_98"/> loan and their support of the
                    enterprise was invited. This notification and invitation included Japan and
                    Russia. As the reform is one in which all the leading powers are alike
                    interested, the United States has steadily favored the widest possible
                    international participation both in the loan and in the reform. The financial
                    details are, however, properly subject to the decision of the bankers
                    concerned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
